## Test Scenario 4 — Batch Creation with Test Resumes

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is the core test. You'll create a batch using both test resumes against a sample job description.

### Step-by-step:

| # | Step | Expected Result |
|---|------|-----------------|
| 1 | Click **"+ New Batch"** button on dashboard | `CreateBatchModal` opens with backdrop blur + slide-up animation |
| 2 | Verify modal fields | Two sections: **Job Description** textarea + **Resume Files** drop zone |
| 3 | Type < 50 chars in the JD field | Counter shows "X more characters needed" |
| 4 | Paste the sample JD below (or your own, 50+ chars) | Counter changes to "✓ Ready" in green |
| 5 | Drag & drop **both PDFs** from `test/` folder into the drop zone | Both files appear in the file list: `Aarav_Sharma_ATS_Resume.pdf` and `Priya_Mehta_ATS_Resume.pdf` |
| 6 | Alternatively, click **"or browse files"** and select both PDFs | Same result — 2 files listed |
| 7 | Try removing one file via the ✕ button | File removed from list, count updates |
| 8 | Re-add the removed file | File list shows 2 files again |
| 9 | Click **"Create & Upload"** | Button shows spinner + "Creating…" text. Modal closes on success |
| 10 | Verify batch appears in `BatchList` | New batch card with status **"Created"** and "2 candidates" |

### Sample Job Description for Testing

```
We are looking for a Full Stack Developer with at least 2 years of experience
in React.js, Node.js, and Python. The ideal candidate should have experience
with cloud platforms (AWS or GCP), RESTful API design, and database management
(SQL and NoSQL). Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to work in an
agile environment are essential. A Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or
related field is preferred.
```

