## Test Scenario 7 — Bias Report View

| # | Step | Expected Result |
|---|------|-----------------|
| 1 | Switch to the **"Bias Report"** tab | `BiasReportView` renders with full analysis |
| 2 | **Fairness Score Cards** | Two side-by-side cards: "Before Anonymization" and "After Skill-Based Ranking" |
| 3 | Verify **Before score** | Shows original fairness score (pre-anonymization) — typically lower |
| 4 | Verify **After score** | Shows AptiCore-optimized score — should be **higher** |
| 5 | Score cards animate on reveal | Animated count-up effect for both scores |
| 6 | **Improvements section** | Lists specific metrics with before/after bars |
| 7 | Check improvement metrics | Metrics like "Gender Parity", "College Bias Reduction", "Location Bias Reduction" |
| 8 | Verify **delta values** | Positive deltas shown in green (improvement), neutral in gray |
| 9 | **Distribution Analysis** section | Three charts: Gender Distribution, College Tier, Location Type |
| 10 | Verify distribution charts render | Bar/pie charts (Recharts) showing post-anonymization distributions |

### Expected Bias Patterns with Test Resumes

With only 2 candidates, distributions will be limited, but the system should still:
- ✅ Show a fairness score delta (before → after)
- ✅ Show anonymization removed name/college/location-based bias signals
- ✅ Generate improvement descriptions explaining what changed
- ✅ Render distribution charts even with 2 data points

